Nanette Comstock https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nanette_Comstock 0 Nanette Comstock (July 17, 1866 – June 24, 1942) was an American actress whose career on stage spanned nearly thirty-five years. She appeared on both the New York and London stage and had shared the stage with many of the luminaries of the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries.
